    "dataclassification": {},
    "description": "This is a clone of issue RHEL-4139 to use for version rhel-9.7.z\n--\nOriginal description:\nDescription of problem:\n\nIf Gnome terminal kept running for many days / months it is getting crashed and resulted in segfault. \n\nVersion-Release number of selected component (if applicable):\n\ngnome-terminal-3.28.2-3.el7.x86_64\n\nHow reproducible:\n\nFrequently\n\nSteps to Reproduce:\n1.Start the gnome-terminal\n2.Run the command / application like \"TOP\",\"HTOP\" for many weeks / months.\n3.Suddenly the gnome-terminal crashes\n\nActual results:\n\nGnome-terminal is crashing if kept running / used for longer period of time.\n\nExpected results:\n\nGnome-terminal should be able to run continuously without any issue. \n\nAdditional info:",
